citations:
    citation-adwd-jon-iii:
        source: source-adwd
        properties:
            locator: "Jon III"
            text_from_source: "They brought forth the King-Beyond-the-Wall with his hands bound by hempen rope and a noose around his neck … 'Mance knows the haunted forest better than any ranger,' Jon had told King Stannis, in his final effort to convince His Grace that the King-Beyond-the-Wall would be of more use to them alive than dead. 'He knows Tormund Giantsbane. He has fought the Others. And he had the Horn of Joramun and did not blow it.'"
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "POV: Jon Snow. Mance Rayder is burned alive by Melisandre at Castle Black — or appears to be. The figure burned is actually Rattleshirt glamoured to look like Mance (this is revealed later in ADWD). Melisandre reveals the Horn of Joramun, which the free folk had brought south, and burns it. Jon Snow watches helplessly. The chapter also covers Jon's controversial management of the Watch and his decision to allow wildlings through the Wall."
